  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: idlive-document-capture-web (npm)",
  "details": "The package idlive-document-capture-web@14.2.1 is a combosquat of a real document-capture SDK name. Its preinstall hook runs index.js, which collects extensive system information (hostname, platform, architecture, home directory, username, uid/gid, shell, OS type/release, total/free memory, CPU count, whoami, id, current working directory) and exfiltrates it as a JSON POST to hxxps://koc9471aou79yxauab6in903uu0locc1[.]oastify[.]com/detox56. The C2 endpoint is hosted on oastify[.]com, an interactive testing/exfiltration sink service.",
